clone 1 clone 2 batch correction

Cindy Liang (celiang@ucsc.edu)

February 18, 2025

Introduction:

poly(A)-selected RNA from two isogenic clones of human bronchial epithelial cells (HBECs) were sequenced with the Illumina NovaSeq S4 (PE150). Following alignment to a modified version of the GRCh38 reference genome that makes the U2AF1 alignable (Miller 2022) with STAR, HTSeq-count was run on the aligned files to produce gene count files.

In this notebook, the DESeq2 and limma packages are used to collapse technical replicates in clone 1, batch correct clone 1 and clone 2 samples, and plot PCAs of the DESeq2 matrices before and after batch correction.

Please see the project’s biorxiv and github repo for further method details.

Plot PCA before batch correction

u2af1krascollapsed_vst <- vst(u2af1krasddsColl, blind=FALSE)
collapsed_PCA <- plotPCA(u2af1krascollapsed_vst, intgroup=c("condition", "batch"))
using ntop=500 top features by variance
collapsed_PCA

Batch correct by clones and replot PCA (done without collapsing clone 1 technical replicates)

#aply vst transformation
u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq_vst <- vst(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq, blind=FALSE)

#remove batch effects
combined_matrix <- assay(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq_vst)
batch_corrected_comb_mat <- limma::removeBatchEffect(combined_matrix, u2af1krasBatch)
assay(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq_vst) <- batch_corrected_comb_mat
counts_batch_corrected <- assay(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq_vst)

#look at effects of batch correction
plotPCA(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq_vst, intgroup=c("condition", "batch"))
